## Mocking Rules

### Unit Tests — Mock Everything External
```python
@pytest.fixture
def mock_gemini(mocker):
    """Mock at the class level — not the function level."""
    return mocker.patch(
        'src.generate.v1_generator.GeminiClient',
        return_value=AsyncMock(
            generate=AsyncMock(return_value=MOCK_GOOD_AD_RESPONSE)
        )
    )

@pytest.fixture
def mock_claude(mocker):
    return mocker.patch(
        'src.evaluate.judge.ClaudeClient',
        return_value=AsyncMock(
            generate=AsyncMock(return_value=MOCK_PASSING_EVALUATION)
        )
    )
```

### Integration Tests — Mock APIs, Never Mock DB
```python
# Real database — always
@pytest.fixture
async def test_db():
    engine = create_async_engine(settings.database_url_test)
    async with engine.begin() as conn:
        await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)
    yield AdLibrary(engine)
    async with engine.begin() as conn:
        await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.drop_all)

# Mocked APIs — always
@pytest.fixture
def mock_all_llm_clients(mock_gemini, mock_claude):
    return mock_gemini, mock_claude
```

